com.amazonaws.android.cognito
Class DefaultCognitoSyncClient

java.lang.Object
  com.amazonaws.android.cognito.DefaultCognitoSyncClient
All Implemented Interfaces:
CognitoSyncClient, CognitoCredentialsProvider.IdentityChangedListener
public class DefaultCognitoSyncClient
extends Object
implements CognitoSyncClient, CognitoCredentialsProvider.IdentityChangedListener

Default implementation of CognitoSyncClient. It saves Dataset in SQLite database. Here is a sample usage: 

 CognitoCredentialsProvider provider = new CognitoCredentialsProvider(context,
         awsAccountId, identityPoolId, unauthRoleArn, authRoleArn);
 CognitoClient client = new DefaultCognitoClient(context, identityPoolId, provider);
 
 Dataset dataset = client.openOrCreateDataset("default_dataset");
 dataset.put("high_score", "100");
 dataset.synchronize(new SyncCallback() {
     // override callbacks
 });

openOrCreateDataset

public com.amazonaws.android.cognito.DefaultDataset openOrCreateDataset(String datasetName)
Description copied from interface: CognitoSyncClient
Opens or creates a dataset. If the dataset doesn't exist, an empty one with the given name will be created. Otherwise, dataset is loaded from local storage. If a dataset is marked as deleted but hasn't been deleted on remote via CognitoSyncClient.refreshDatasetMetadata(), it will throw IllegalStateException.

Specified by:
openOrCreateDataset in interface CognitoSyncClient
Parameters:
datasetName - dataset name, must be [a-zA-Z0=9_.:-]+
Returns:
dataset loaded from local storage

wipeData

public void wipeData()
Description copied from interface: CognitoSyncClient
Wipes all user data cached locally, including identity id, session credentials, dataset metadata, and all records. Any data that hasn't been synced will be lost. This method is usually used when customer logs out.
